1
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:09,000
You've had him follow me
since we separated.

2
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,000
Are you a psychopath?

3
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,199
Why are you doing this?

4
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:16,159
I'm doing all this because I love you.

5
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,199
If I can't be happy, then no one will be.

6
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,960
If I wasn't indecisive,

7
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:23,960
if I had been firm…

8
00:02:25,199 --> 00:02:28,000
I wouldn't have made the wrong choice.

9
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,680
She didn't really love him.

10
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,960
I'm just a product of their mistake.

11
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,360
Am I supposed to give up

12
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:36,400
and be a coward like you?

13
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,960
And behave immorally like you?

14
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,400
-I can't do it.
-Tarn!

15
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:45,000
I already have plenty of friends.

16
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,159
But now,

17
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:49,240
I want you.

18
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,000
Happy birthday, Nut.

19
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,560
We made you a cake.

20
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,399
What decoration do you want
on your cake this year?

21
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,720
I want a rainbow.

22
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,720
With these colors please, Mom.

23
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:10,079
That looks hard.

24
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:12,839
You need to help me then.

25
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,279
All right.

26
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:17,319
You are a boy.
You shouldn't like pastel rainbows.

27
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:18,959
It's silly.

28
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,600
You should teach him right from wrong.

29
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,920
Don't spoil him.

30
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,399
Nut.

31
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,759
How about we pick a new pattern?

32
00:06:06,839 --> 00:06:08,279
How about an ocean?

33
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,560
Nut.

34
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,959
What pattern would you like
on your birthday cake?

35
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,199
Anything is fine, Mom.

36
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,639
Can you put a piece in a box for me?

37
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,120
I want my friend to try it.

38
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:23,240
Sure.

39
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,399
Look at the activities you do.

40
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,199
Don't you know how to do
any manly activities?

41
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,319
It might be almost 20 years late.

42
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:53,600
But I still want to do this for you.

43
00:07:56,879 --> 00:07:59,240
I may have made mistakes in the past.

44
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,319
But please know that…

45
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:09,360
you are not one of them.

46
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,600
You are my gift.

47
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:19,000
Happy birthday.

48
00:08:49,559 --> 00:08:51,279
I'm not too late, am I?

49
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,120
Happy birthday, Nut.

50
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,759
I wish you happiness.

51
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
Thank you.

52
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,480
-Sure.
-Let's go inside.

53
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,559
It might seem a little old,

54
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:23,840
but doesn't it look like
the teddy bear you lost?

55
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:26,639
Yes, it really does.

56
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:46,320
I didn't think I would find a teddy bear

57
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,919
similar to your last one.

58
00:09:49,799 --> 00:09:51,120
I was lucky, I guess.

59
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:08,120
Do you know

60
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,519
that I worked really hard to find it?

61
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:15,559
I put in a lot of effort.

62
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,360
The same goes for the feelings

63
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:22,840
that I have for you.

64
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,879
I know

65
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:34,039
that we haven't known
each other for so long.

66
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,759
It might be too early

67
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:40,279
for me to be saying this.

68
00:10:42,519 --> 00:10:45,480
But I can't let any more time pass by.

69
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,080
On my first day at work,

70
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,440
you scolded those drunks for me.

71
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,879
You looked so damn cool.

72
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:01,879
I became your fan after that day.

73
00:11:03,399 --> 00:11:05,039
Although you pretended not to care,

74
00:11:05,559 --> 00:11:07,080
ignored me,

75
00:11:07,159 --> 00:11:09,159
and had that confused look on your face,

76
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,440
your heart was filled with warmth

77
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,559
and I couldn't stop myself
from falling for you.

78
00:11:24,159 --> 00:11:25,200
I didn't know

79
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:28,480
the best way to confess my feelings,

80
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:32,519
so I bought you this special gift.

81
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,759
Thank you so much

82
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,159
for this special gift, Prib.

83
00:11:46,559 --> 00:11:50,360
However, no matter how similar
this teddy bear is to my old one,

84
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:53,240
I can't accept it.

85
00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:01,159
Prib.

86
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,240
You know that I don't feel the same way.

87
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,600
I understand.

88
00:12:18,879 --> 00:12:20,240
I know

89
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:23,159
that I can't change your mind.

90
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,480
I just wanted to show you

91
00:12:30,799 --> 00:12:32,279
how serious I am about you.

92
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,399
It's okay

93
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,720
if you feel differently.

94
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,519
It's okay

95
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,440
if you don't love me.

96
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,960
I'm okay.

97
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,279
Prib.

98
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,919
I came to wish you a happy birthday.

99
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:18,399
I wish you all the happiness in the world.

100
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:34,759
Even though
I can't be that someone for you,

101
00:13:36,279 --> 00:13:37,360
-we can still--
-Stop.

102
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,960
I know what you are going to say.

103
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,960
You're going to say

104
00:13:57,039 --> 00:13:59,159
that I can be your sister, right?

105
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,600
Can you?

106
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,120
I'm not ready right now.

107
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:26,039
But I will be.

108
00:15:07,399 --> 00:15:08,600
Prib.

109
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:14,960
Shall we go home?

110
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:17,840
It's okay.

111
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,440
I got here on my own.

112
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:22,279
I can go home alone as well.

113
00:15:24,919 --> 00:15:25,799
I'll be all right.

114
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,639
Are you all right?

115
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,240
Yes.

116
00:15:40,759 --> 00:15:42,360
I'm okay.

117
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:48,000
You're not okay.

118
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,279
You're eating barbecue with a teddy bear.

119
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,720
Are you sure you're okay? Are you?

120
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:58,240
I'm hungry.

121
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:01,320
And I'm sad.

122
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,600
I saw her holding the teddy bear

123
00:16:09,679 --> 00:16:11,159
and tripping over

124
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,000
in front of the restaurant,

125
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,480
so I called you.

126
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:19,919
Prib.

127
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,600
What are you going to do
with that teddy bear?

128
00:16:23,759 --> 00:16:26,000
I'm going to donate it.

129
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,840
Nut doesn't want it.

130
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:33,519
But I'm sure somebody
will want it one day.

131
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,320
All right then.

132
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,919
Cheer up. Somebody will want you
one day too.

133
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,559
Right?

134
00:16:43,639 --> 00:16:46,200
I'm beautiful, kind, and cute.

135
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:48,000
Plus, I've got time for him.

136
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,279
How can nobody want me?

137
00:16:55,559 --> 00:16:57,320
Why am I so unlucky?

138
00:16:57,399 --> 00:17:00,679
I always end up in the friend zone.

139
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:08,119
Prib, your soulmate might be a foreigner.

140
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,440
A foreign creature from another world.

141
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:18,079
Being his friend

142
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,880
is better than being a stranger.

143
00:17:21,759 --> 00:17:22,839
That's right.

144
00:17:23,559 --> 00:17:25,839
You are better off as his friend.

145
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,440
The bond will last longer.

146
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,799
Are you comforting me or rubbing it in?

147
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,640
I'm comforting you.

148
00:17:35,319 --> 00:17:36,279
I love you.

149
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,559
Eat this.

150
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,720
It will keep you quiet.

151
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,880
It's hot.

152
00:17:44,039 --> 00:17:45,599
I love you too, mister.

153
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,799
Wait, what?

154
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,759
What a sneaky little bastard.

155
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,160
Stop.

156
00:18:00,039 --> 00:18:01,240
You can drink,

157
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:02,960
but don't throw up like last time.

158
00:18:56,559 --> 00:18:58,200
What are you doing, Nut?

159
00:19:00,799 --> 00:19:01,640
Well…

160
00:19:02,119 --> 00:19:03,960
I'm recording this moment like you do.

161
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,119
You're recording it?

162
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,480
Then I should be in it too.

163
00:19:23,839 --> 00:19:24,839
Thank you

164
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,559
for throwing me a birthday party.

165
00:19:29,319 --> 00:19:30,559
Do you like it?

166
00:19:32,319 --> 00:19:33,160
Yes.

167
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:35,599
Do you like the party

168
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,519
or me?

169
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:41,559
What a cheap shot.

170
00:19:43,319 --> 00:19:44,599
Well…

171
00:19:45,359 --> 00:19:46,519
I like both of them.

172
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,160
What about the teddy bear?

173
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,359
Did you not like it?

174
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,720
No.

175
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,119
It kind of freaked me out.

176
00:19:59,599 --> 00:20:01,319
How could they look so similar?

177
00:20:03,039 --> 00:20:04,359
But the truth is

178
00:20:05,359 --> 00:20:06,559
their colors,

179
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:09,000
eyes,

180
00:20:10,119 --> 00:20:11,559
and smells were different.

181
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,279
And most importantly,

182
00:20:17,039 --> 00:20:18,400
it wasn't as warm to hug.

183
00:20:22,359 --> 00:20:24,079
That's why you didn't like it.

184
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:26,680
Yes.

185
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,839
Despite their similarities,

186
00:20:33,359 --> 00:20:35,039
the teddy bear is irreplaceable.

187
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:39,680
What if

188
00:20:41,279 --> 00:20:42,640
it's me?

189
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:45,799
Am I good enough
to replace your teddy bear?

190
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,079
You are you.

191
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,119
You can't replace anyone.

192
00:20:57,359 --> 00:20:59,319
When you asked me what I wanted

193
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,480
for my birthday

194
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:03,799
and I said nothing,

195
00:21:08,359 --> 00:21:09,799
that's because

196
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,480
I already have you.

197
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,079
Stay by my side…

198
00:21:24,319 --> 00:21:25,599
and don't go anywhere.

199
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:51,079
What did you do, Tofu?

200
00:21:52,119 --> 00:21:54,680
It's how adults make promises.

201
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,319
I promise

202
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,640
to be with you forever.

203
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:04,559
In that case…

204
00:22:06,279 --> 00:22:07,359
please stay

205
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,480
with me tonight.

206
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,759
What a wonderful night.

207
00:22:40,799 --> 00:22:42,920
I've become Nut's special someone.

208
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:47,000
And I'm going back to Nut's room.

209
00:23:57,079 --> 00:23:58,119
Hey.

210
00:23:59,799 --> 00:24:01,039
You weren't sleeping.

211
00:24:01,519 --> 00:24:03,039
I was curious to see

212
00:24:03,119 --> 00:24:04,319
what you were going to do.

213
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:07,079
Why didn't you wake me up?

214
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,359
Well…

215
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:14,400
I wanted to stay like this.

216
00:24:19,599 --> 00:24:20,519
Thank you

217
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,480
for coming here.

218
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,599
Thank you for caring about me.

219
00:24:28,759 --> 00:24:30,480
Thank you for everything.

220
00:24:33,519 --> 00:24:34,759
Without you,

221
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:38,480
I'm not sure
if I would have gotten through it.

222
00:24:41,559 --> 00:24:43,039
Your mom said

223
00:24:44,359 --> 00:24:46,559
love isn't about doing
something for someone.

224
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,640
It's about putting your heart into it.

225
00:24:53,559 --> 00:24:55,519
My heart is all yours.

226
00:24:59,359 --> 00:25:01,240
Yes, I know.

227
00:25:10,279 --> 00:25:12,160
I wish we could stay this way forever.

228
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:17,559
You smell nice.

229
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,319
So does your hair.

230
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,799
But I think

231
00:25:42,759 --> 00:25:43,920
you stink.

232
00:25:46,559 --> 00:25:47,640
It's your hair.

233
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:49,960
Smell it.

234
00:25:55,599 --> 00:25:57,119
It doesn't stink.

235
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,279
It stinks.

236
00:26:02,359 --> 00:26:03,599
It doesn't.

237
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,039
Trust me. It stinks.

238
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,960
Go take a shower.

239
00:26:11,119 --> 00:26:12,440
I'll wash your hair for you.

240
00:27:10,359 --> 00:27:11,559
Kuenchai.

241
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:12,880
Kuenchai.

242
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,440
Kuenchai, come eat.

243
00:27:26,799 --> 00:27:27,799
I'm leaving, Mom.

244
00:27:28,519 --> 00:27:29,440
Okay.

245
00:27:32,759 --> 00:27:33,599
I'm leaving.

246
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,160
Did you forget something?

247
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:44,839
What?

248
00:27:46,799 --> 00:27:48,079
Your lunchbox.

249
00:28:12,279 --> 00:28:13,279
Thank you.

250
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,559
I'll get going then.

251
00:28:26,599 --> 00:28:27,759
I realized

252
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,640
why people were yearning for love.

253
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:33,720
Love is a wonderful thing.

254
00:28:34,839 --> 00:28:37,960
It's so wonderful that I don't want
to be a teddy bear again.

255
00:29:13,559 --> 00:29:15,680
Prib, are you heartbroken again?

256
00:29:15,759 --> 00:29:17,440
You're drawing men.

257
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:20,519
Yes, I'm permanently heartbroken.

258
00:29:22,839 --> 00:29:25,240
Did you confess your feelings to that guy?

259
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:28,160
Yes, we talked it out.

260
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:31,279
Are you sad?

261
00:29:32,759 --> 00:29:34,640
It's no use being sad.

262
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,720
I better put my time into something else.

263
00:29:36,799 --> 00:29:38,759
I have an important mission.

264
00:29:38,839 --> 00:29:40,480
What are you talking about?

265
00:29:44,039 --> 00:29:46,880
I'm going to find that person for Tarn.

266
00:29:48,519 --> 00:29:49,839
Perhaps,

267
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:52,599
I was born for this.

268
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,440
You…

269
00:30:09,559 --> 00:30:11,319
Kuenchai, come and eat.

270
00:30:15,839 --> 00:30:17,440
You already gave him his food.

271
00:30:19,559 --> 00:30:20,880
Did I?

272
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,279
When?

273
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,799
What's wrong, Tofu?

274
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:46,559
You were happy this morning.

275
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:49,759
It's Mrs. Na.

276
00:31:51,319 --> 00:31:52,599
Lately,

277
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,359
she has been forgetful.

278
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,519
She forgot that she had fed Kuenchai
this morning.

279
00:31:58,039 --> 00:31:59,440
And this book,

280
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,880
she has been reading the same page.

281
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:07,839
Maybe it's…

282
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:12,319
The medicine makes her…

283
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:14,279
Is everyone okay?

284
00:32:14,359 --> 00:32:15,200
Well…

285
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,119
I'm sorry.

286
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,839
I guess I didn't get enough sleep.

287
00:32:20,319 --> 00:32:22,119
I was going to say

