00:56:35,519 --> 00:56:38,000
You don't even know how to do laundry.

575
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:52,840
I'm sorry.

576
00:56:52,920 --> 00:56:56,119
-You're sorry?
-Nut.

577
00:56:56,719 --> 00:56:58,039
-Nut.
-Tofu.

578
00:56:58,119 --> 00:56:59,320
Tofu.

579
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:39,719
I have to shower again.

580
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:43,960
Ask Kuenchai who started the fight.

581
00:57:49,639 --> 00:57:51,920
-Yes, Juea.
-I need your advice.

582
00:57:53,679 --> 00:57:56,199
Don't ask questions. Come now.

583
00:57:56,760 --> 00:57:57,840
All right.

584
00:57:59,639 --> 00:58:00,920
I'm going to the office.

585
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:02,599
Okay.

586
00:58:10,400 --> 00:58:12,199
Nut is so cute.

587
00:58:17,800 --> 00:58:18,960
Mr. Rocking Chair.

588
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:22,320
Ms. Sofa.

589
00:58:23,760 --> 00:58:24,679
Ms. Phone.

590
00:58:25,320 --> 00:58:26,400
Are you still sleeping?

591
00:58:26,480 --> 00:58:27,800
I'm so sleepy.

592
00:58:27,880 --> 00:58:29,840
I don't want to get up.

593
00:58:33,280 --> 00:58:34,760
Ms. Phone.

594
00:58:38,320 --> 00:58:39,480
Ms. Phone.

595
00:58:41,159 --> 00:58:42,280
What are you doing?

596
00:58:45,440 --> 00:58:47,239
It went off.

597
00:58:47,320 --> 00:58:48,760
I was going to charge it.

598
00:58:48,840 --> 00:58:52,239
I've been trying to charge it
since yesterday, but it won't work.

599
00:58:52,960 --> 00:58:54,440
I guess it's broken.

600
00:58:58,239 --> 00:58:59,159
Kuenchai.

601
00:58:59,880 --> 00:59:01,199
He's digging again.

602
00:59:06,360 --> 00:59:07,519
Is it possible

603
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:09,920
that Ms. Phone fell asleep too?

604
00:59:11,639 --> 00:59:12,760
What about me?

605
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:15,920
How much time do I have left?

606
00:59:24,519 --> 00:59:27,599
Kids are so rude these days.

607
00:59:29,639 --> 00:59:30,559
Oh, my…

608
00:59:30,639 --> 00:59:32,960
There must be a thunderstorm.

609
00:59:33,039 --> 00:59:37,000
My niece is working early in the morn…

610
00:59:38,159 --> 00:59:39,239
You're not working.

611
00:59:39,800 --> 00:59:41,400
What are you looking at?

612
00:59:43,079 --> 00:59:45,719
Doesn't the guy with the book

613
00:59:45,800 --> 00:59:47,119
seem familiar to you?

614
00:59:50,039 --> 00:59:51,159
No.

615
00:59:51,239 --> 00:59:53,199
Look carefully.

616
00:59:53,280 --> 00:59:56,800
Why do his nails, joints, and finger hair

617
00:59:56,880 --> 00:59:58,280
look familiar to me?

618
00:59:59,159 --> 01:00:02,360
These fingers definitely belong
to a handsome person.

619
01:00:02,440 --> 01:00:06,679
How are the fingers of a handsome man
and an ugly man different?

620
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:07,599
Well…

621
01:00:08,119 --> 01:00:09,480
This means

622
01:00:09,559 --> 01:00:10,400
I am

623
01:00:10,480 --> 01:00:12,880
really damn handsome.

624
01:00:15,639 --> 01:00:17,000
Seriously?

625
01:00:17,079 --> 01:00:18,280
They are so different.

626
01:00:18,840 --> 01:00:20,039
Your fingers

627
01:00:20,119 --> 01:00:22,239
-are so tanned.
-Prib.

628
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:23,159
Hey.

629
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:27,800
Why is he covering his face with a book?

630
01:00:27,880 --> 01:00:28,840
I don't know.

631
01:00:28,920 --> 01:00:30,000
If I run into him,

632
01:00:30,079 --> 01:00:33,880
I'll ask him why he's trying
to hide his face.

633
01:00:33,960 --> 01:00:36,800
Instead of looking at his fingers,

634
01:00:36,880 --> 01:00:41,039
why don't you ask
his friends or relatives?

635
01:00:41,920 --> 01:00:45,519
Is it possible that he's an orphan?

636
01:00:45,599 --> 01:00:48,039
He's an orphan with relatives.

637
01:00:48,880 --> 01:00:49,719
I see.

638
01:00:50,519 --> 01:00:52,559
That's right.

639
01:00:52,639 --> 01:00:54,599
I'll ask his relatives.

640
01:00:54,679 --> 01:00:56,440
Please move.

641
01:00:57,000 --> 01:00:58,760
Aren't you going to work?

642
01:00:59,679 --> 01:01:00,679
Gosh.

643
01:01:01,519 --> 01:01:03,119
-Nut.
-Juea, hello.

644
01:01:03,199 --> 01:01:04,119
Hello.

645
01:01:04,199 --> 01:01:07,360
Can you give me
the location of the school?

646
01:01:07,440 --> 01:01:08,480
And the mall

647
01:01:08,559 --> 01:01:10,039
didn't give us their permission.

648
01:01:10,679 --> 01:01:13,559
-Okay.
-Let's talk inside. Come on.

649
01:01:14,440 --> 01:01:15,480
Wait.

650
01:01:18,039 --> 01:01:19,840
-Juea.
-Hold on.

651
01:01:24,079 --> 01:01:25,159
What are you doing?

652
01:01:30,280 --> 01:01:34,119
All men's hands look the same.
I shouldn't suspect anything.

653
01:01:34,719 --> 01:01:35,840
Come on, Nut.

654
01:01:36,360 --> 01:01:38,440
Okay, Prib. I'll send it to you.

655
01:01:38,519 --> 01:01:42,119
But I don't know how much
he knows about Tatarn.

656
01:01:42,199 --> 01:01:45,199
As far as I know,
their relationship wasn't going well.

657
01:01:45,280 --> 01:01:47,039
It's okay.

658
01:01:47,119 --> 01:01:49,159
It's worth a shot.

659
01:01:49,840 --> 01:01:51,360
Thank you, Mr. Anik.

660
01:01:51,840 --> 01:01:53,039
You're welcome.

661
01:01:53,960 --> 01:01:55,480
Let's go, Dad.

662
01:01:55,559 --> 01:01:56,719
Let's go.

663
01:01:56,800 --> 01:01:57,880
Where are we going?

664
01:01:57,960 --> 01:01:59,360
I've booked us a table.

665
01:01:59,440 --> 01:02:01,119
-Let's go.
-Yes.

666
01:02:09,639 --> 01:02:10,800
Yes, Lieutenant Kong.

667
01:02:12,280 --> 01:02:13,199
What?

668
01:02:20,159 --> 01:02:21,480
You can go to work.

669
01:02:21,559 --> 01:02:22,920
Don't worry about me.

670
01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:24,199
I can go with a friend.

671
01:02:25,880 --> 01:02:27,320
We can go next time.

672
01:02:27,400 --> 01:02:29,199
I'm coming back next week.

673
01:02:32,679 --> 01:02:34,360
Be honest with me.

674
01:02:35,199 --> 01:02:36,840
Are you so involved in this case

675
01:02:37,400 --> 01:02:38,679
because it's Neung's friend?

676
01:03:20,039 --> 01:03:21,159
Mister.

677
01:03:21,239 --> 01:03:22,079
Where are you?

678
01:03:22,159 --> 01:03:24,239
I'm at the hospital.

679
01:03:25,880 --> 01:03:26,840
What happened?

680
01:03:29,039 --> 01:03:30,320
I'm fine.

681
01:03:37,280 --> 01:03:38,679
Song.

682
01:03:38,760 --> 01:03:39,719
Song.

683
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:40,639
Song.

684
01:03:42,880 --> 01:03:44,599
Why are you at the hospital then?

685
01:03:44,679 --> 01:03:47,840
I was selling an ad nearby,
so I came to visit my mom.

686
01:03:48,679 --> 01:03:50,000
Is something wrong?

687
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:57,440
What's with you?

688
01:03:57,960 --> 01:03:59,960
I prepared you very well.

689
01:04:00,519 --> 01:04:02,199
How did this happen?

690
01:04:02,760 --> 01:04:04,280
What did you say to your dad?

691
01:04:06,599 --> 01:04:08,239
He ditched me for work

692
01:04:08,719 --> 01:04:10,559
before I could say anything.

693
01:04:11,199 --> 01:04:12,840
Don't be such a crybaby.

694
01:04:12,920 --> 01:04:14,280
Your dad is a cop.

695
01:04:14,360 --> 01:04:16,400
He had an urgent case.

696
01:04:17,400 --> 01:04:19,159
You've been his son for 18 years.

697
01:04:19,239 --> 01:04:20,880
You should get it by now.

698
01:04:22,039 --> 01:04:24,840
I wouldn't mind
if he went to work on another case.

699
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:27,360
But the victim

700
01:04:27,440 --> 01:04:28,920
is Neung's friend.

701
01:04:29,719 --> 01:04:31,880
Neung always comes first for him.

702
01:04:34,199 --> 01:04:35,719
That's crazy.

703
01:04:35,800 --> 01:04:36,719
You think too much.

704
01:04:37,719 --> 01:04:38,960
It's true.

705
01:04:39,039 --> 01:04:40,599
Neung was his favorite

706
01:04:41,079 --> 01:04:42,639
ever since I was a baby.

707
01:04:44,480 --> 01:04:47,840
He was handsome, smart, athletic,

708
01:04:47,920 --> 01:04:51,440
into music, popular,
and good at everything.

709
01:04:53,599 --> 01:04:55,119
When Neung died,

710
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:58,400
Dad's hope died along with him.

711
01:05:05,039 --> 01:05:06,760
I'm just someone

712
01:05:07,239 --> 01:05:08,840
he neglects.

713
01:05:09,920 --> 01:05:11,440
No matter how hard I try,

714
01:05:12,079 --> 01:05:14,159
I can only be Neung's shadow.

715
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:26,480
All parents

716
01:05:27,800 --> 01:05:29,440
love their children the same way.

717
01:05:30,199 --> 01:05:31,360
That's not true.

718
01:05:32,920 --> 01:05:35,239
Maybe they love their children equally,

719
01:05:35,320 --> 01:05:37,519
but not in the same way.

720
01:05:41,920 --> 01:05:43,960
I'm sorry for eavesdropping.

721
01:05:44,039 --> 01:05:46,440
The conversation happens
to be about family,

722
01:05:46,519 --> 01:05:49,559
so I'm hoping to give you
my opinion as a mother.

723
01:05:56,320 --> 01:05:58,559
Parents can't love
their children the same way

724
01:05:59,119 --> 01:06:01,320
because every child is different.

725
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:04,679
Some children who can take good care
of themselves

726
01:06:04,760 --> 01:06:07,119
may be neglected by their parents.

727
01:06:07,800 --> 01:06:11,000
But some children
who can't take care of themselves

728
01:06:11,760 --> 01:06:14,599
require more attention from the parents.

729
01:06:15,440 --> 01:06:17,440
Because parents treat them differently,

730
01:06:17,519 --> 01:06:20,639
children tend to think that parents
love their children unequally.

731
01:06:20,719 --> 01:06:22,400
The truth is

732
01:06:22,480 --> 01:06:26,000
they just love and care about
their children in different ways.

733
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:28,239
That's right.

734
01:06:28,320 --> 01:06:29,639
I express my love

735
01:06:29,719 --> 01:06:32,000
towards my parents differently.

736
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:34,760
But I love both of them.

737
01:06:36,679 --> 01:06:39,039
I talk to each of them

738
01:06:39,119 --> 01:06:41,039
about certain things.

739
01:06:45,679 --> 01:06:47,920
The fact that your father
gives you freedom

740
01:06:48,480 --> 01:06:51,280
doesn't mean he doesn't love
or care about you.

741
01:06:52,199 --> 01:06:55,159
It's because he trusts you.

742
01:06:57,440 --> 01:07:00,360
Your father has stuff he needs to work on,

743
01:07:01,159 --> 01:07:04,760
but you do too.

744
01:07:10,360 --> 01:07:11,639
You always

745
01:07:11,719 --> 01:07:14,320
compare yourself to your brother.

746
01:07:15,039 --> 01:07:16,400
You want to be as good as him,

747
01:07:17,360 --> 01:07:18,840
so your dad would praise you.

748
01:07:21,320 --> 01:07:23,159
You don't need to be like anyone.

749
01:07:24,199 --> 01:07:25,960
Just be yourself.

750
01:07:26,440 --> 01:07:28,320
You are second to none.

751
01:07:33,400 --> 01:07:34,440
Thank you

752
01:07:34,519 --> 01:07:36,480
for reminding me.

753
01:07:37,039 --> 01:07:38,320
You're welcome.

754
01:07:41,000 --> 01:07:42,280
Can I

755
01:07:42,960 --> 01:07:44,440
hug you?

756
01:07:45,039 --> 01:07:47,039
I don't have a mother to hug.

757
01:07:49,639 --> 01:07:50,519
Of course.

758
01:07:50,599 --> 01:07:51,840
Gen's friends

759
01:07:51,920 --> 01:07:54,119
are like my own children.

760
01:08:05,119 --> 01:08:06,320
That's enough.

761
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:07,440
You sneaky punk.

762
01:08:08,280 --> 01:08:09,920
He's being protective of me.

763
01:08:16,760 --> 01:08:19,279
Mom, are you not coming home with me?

764
01:08:19,359 --> 01:08:23,199
-I'm not going back to the office.
-I have to meet two more patients.

765
01:08:23,279 --> 01:08:24,800
You can go home first.

766
01:08:26,199 --> 01:08:27,439
I'll see you at home.

767
01:08:27,520 --> 01:08:29,800
I need to check on my patients.

768
01:08:29,880 --> 01:08:32,800
Go home safely, both of you. See you.

769
01:08:39,840 --> 01:08:41,880
Mister, come have dinner with me.

770
01:08:41,960 --> 01:08:43,159
I've booked a table.

771
01:08:47,800 --> 01:08:49,039
Don't you have any friends

772
01:08:49,119 --> 01:08:50,399
other than me?

773
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:54,359
You are not my friend.

774
01:08:54,439 --> 01:08:57,680
Please, come on. Have dinner with me.

775
01:08:58,520 --> 01:08:59,760
Please.

776
01:09:02,920 --> 01:09:03,840
Where is it?

777
01:09:09,800 --> 01:09:11,319
Wait, mister.

778
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:20,199
Ms. Phone has fallen asleep
along with Ms. Sofa and Mr. Right Slipper.

779
01:09:21,560 --> 01:09:23,560
Mr. Rocking Chair looks sleepy too.

780
01:09:25,359 --> 01:09:27,159
Am I going to be next?

781
01:09:27,840 --> 01:09:29,079
Maybe

782
01:09:29,159 --> 01:09:32,239
only the furniture downstairs
is falling asleep.

783
01:09:32,319 --> 01:09:34,960
The rest of us upstairs are fine.

784
01:09:35,640 --> 01:09:38,920
But Mr. Right Slipper
followed Mrs. Na around the house.

785
01:09:39,000 --> 01:09:40,960
He still fell asleep.

786
01:09:41,039 --> 01:09:43,199
Teddy goes around the house too,

787
01:09:43,279 --> 01:09:45,760
so he might fall asleep next.

788
01:09:45,840 --> 01:09:48,840
We don't know why the furniture
is falling asleep.

789
01:09:48,920 --> 01:09:51,560
And you don't know how you became a human.

790
01:09:52,039 --> 01:09:54,680
I don't know if those two things
are related,

791
01:09:54,760 --> 01:09:57,840
but you might be the only one
who can find the answer.

792
01:09:57,920 --> 01:10:02,119
If you discover where you came from,

793
01:10:02,199 --> 01:10:06,840
you might find a way to stay awake,
unlike the others.

794
01:10:06,920 --> 01:10:08,840
Did you find any more clues yesterday?

795
01:10:09,319 --> 01:10:10,439
Yes.

796
01:10:11,119 --> 01:10:12,960
Yesterday, Prib said…

797
01:10:13,840 --> 01:10:16,760
She said it was a tall male student.

798
01:10:19,319 --> 01:10:21,039
After he bought me,

799
01:10:21,640 --> 01:10:23,159
he put a bandana on me.

800
01:10:24,560 --> 01:10:25,680
Excuse me.

801
01:10:25,760 --> 01:10:27,680
I'll take these two items

802
01:10:27,760 --> 01:10:31,319
and please swap the bow
for this pink bandana.

803
01:10:31,880 --> 01:10:33,319
Don't you like the bow?

804
01:10:33,399 --> 01:10:36,520
I want it to be special.

805
01:10:37,039 --> 01:10:38,680
Plus, he likes the color pink.

806
01:10:38,760 --> 01:10:40,399
-All right.
-Thank you.

807
01:10:42,880 --> 01:10:45,560
You hid the teddy's scarf
in my room, didn't you?

808
01:10:46,720 --> 01:10:47,760
Didn't you?

809
01:10:48,640 --> 01:10:49,960
I didn't.

810
01:10:51,840 --> 01:10:53,640
It had fallen, so I put it away.

811
01:10:53,720 --> 01:10:54,880
Don't lie!

812
01:10:55,439 --> 01:10:57,880
You were going through my personal stuff!

813
01:10:57,960 --> 01:10:59,520
What do you want?

814
01:11:00,199 --> 01:11:01,920
The scarf. The book.

815
01:11:02,680 --> 01:11:04,479
Still think it's unrelated?

816
01:11:07,279 --> 01:11:08,359
Could it be…

817
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:17,520
BE WITH YOU

818
01:11:17,600 --> 01:11:22,079
BE WITH YOU

819
01:11:37,159 --> 01:11:38,359
You're home early.

820
01:11:38,439 --> 01:11:40,000
Yes.

821
01:11:40,079 --> 01:11:42,119
I talked to Juea and had a meeting.

822
01:11:42,199 --> 01:11:44,279
I have to write more scenes.

823
01:11:44,359 --> 01:11:46,119
I'm pulling an all-nighter tonight.

824
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:52,600
He's writing about his life.

825
01:11:53,079 --> 01:11:55,159
Even if it's a little sad,

826
01:11:55,640 --> 01:11:57,079
that's okay,

827
01:11:57,159 --> 01:12:00,479
because I'll add sweetness to his life,

828
01:12:03,720 --> 01:12:04,680
There might be clues

829
01:12:05,239 --> 01:12:07,239
about that man in the screenplay.

830
01:12:07,880 --> 01:12:09,279
Then you should get writing.

831
01:12:12,159 --> 01:12:13,039
What's with you?

832
01:12:14,039 --> 01:12:15,359
You usually tell me to rest.

833
01:12:16,560 --> 01:12:17,520
Well,

834
01:12:17,600 --> 01:12:19,319
finish it so you can rest.

835
01:12:19,880 --> 01:12:21,279
Keep on writing.

836
01:12:21,359 --> 01:12:22,720
I'll give you a massage.

837
01:12:25,239 --> 01:12:26,560
You're being weird today.

838
01:12:29,039 --> 01:12:30,439
I might be weird,

839
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:32,680
but I look cute every day.

840
01:12:41,119 --> 01:12:45,119
SCENE 14A. BASKETBALL CLUB.
HIGH SCHOOL. DAYTIME (CONTINUED).

841
01:13:09,159 --> 01:13:11,159
The character Kawee

842
01:13:11,720 --> 01:13:12,840
is sensitive,

843
01:13:12,920 --> 01:13:13,960
not talkative,

844
01:13:14,439 --> 01:13:15,920
introverted,

845
01:13:16,600 --> 01:13:18,520
and not athletic.

846
01:13:19,039 --> 01:13:20,239
That must be Nut.

847
01:13:40,119 --> 01:13:41,239
Song

848
01:13:41,319 --> 01:13:42,560
plays Nont,

849
01:13:42,640 --> 01:13:45,960
the popular basketball player
whom Nut had a crush on.

850
01:13:46,039 --> 01:13:47,319
He didn't like Nut back.

851
01:13:48,199 --> 01:13:49,880
He's probably

852
01:13:51,239 --> 01:13:52,199
Neung,

853
01:13:52,760 --> 01:13:54,199
Song's brother.

854
01:14:48,840 --> 01:14:51,079
The character Tonnam

855
01:14:51,159 --> 01:14:53,039
is Nont's best friend.

856
01:14:58,560 --> 01:15:00,159
Wow, that's beautiful.

857
01:15:01,000 --> 01:15:02,039
Thank you.

858
01:15:06,760 --> 01:15:08,119
Tonnam

859
01:15:08,199 --> 01:15:09,800
is a young and confident thinker

860
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:12,560
who loves to read

861
01:15:13,039 --> 01:15:14,600
and is obsessed with art.

862
01:15:15,920 --> 01:15:17,840
There's only one moon.

863
01:15:18,560 --> 01:15:19,560
Right?

864
01:15:21,399 --> 01:15:23,239
How about I draw another moon?

865
01:15:24,920 --> 01:15:26,680
If you draw another moon,

866
01:15:27,399 --> 01:15:29,760
the first moon will lose its meaning.

867
01:16:21,600 --> 01:16:22,439
TONNAM

868
01:17:28,640 --> 01:17:29,600
Tarn.

869
01:17:30,560 --> 01:17:32,720
Why would you do that?

870
01:17:32,800 --> 01:17:33,720
Why?

871
01:17:33,800 --> 01:17:35,640
-Tarn.
-It's funny.

872
01:17:35,720 --> 01:17:37,520
That hurts.

873
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:40,399
-My ear hurts.
-Did your ear explode?

874
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,159
This "T" guy

875
01:18:08,239 --> 01:18:09,800
is definitely portrayed by Tonnam.

876
01:18:11,119 --> 01:18:14,199
I need to find the person
the character Tonnam is based on.

877
01:18:33,760 --> 01:18:37,680
BASKETBALL TEAM BATCH 128

878
01:18:47,439 --> 01:18:48,680
What are you doing?

879
01:19:00,079 --> 01:19:01,039
You…

880
01:19:06,840 --> 01:19:08,319
Ma'am.

881
01:19:09,039 --> 01:19:09,920
Ma'am.

882
01:19:10,479 --> 01:19:11,800
Are you okay?

883
01:19:23,520 --> 01:19:24,560
Ma'am.

884
01:19:24,640 --> 01:19:25,600
Anont.

885
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:30,319
Are you still wandering here?

886
01:19:30,399 --> 01:19:32,319
You should go to the light.

887
01:19:32,399 --> 01:19:34,279
I'll make merit for you.

888
01:19:34,760 --> 01:19:38,159
-Ma'am, I'm human.
-No…

889
01:19:41,279 --> 01:19:43,760
You've been dead for ten years.

890
01:19:43,840 --> 01:19:45,720
Don't you know?

891
01:19:48,640 --> 01:19:49,880
Sathu.

892
01:19:49,960 --> 01:19:53,239
Ma'am, my name is Tofu, not Anont.

893
01:19:53,319 --> 01:19:55,079
I'm here to shoot the series.

894
01:20:02,880 --> 01:20:04,079
Really?

895
01:20:05,520 --> 01:20:07,000
Are you really human?

896
01:20:07,079 --> 01:20:08,239
Yes.

897
01:20:13,159 --> 01:20:14,800
My heart almost stopped.

898
01:20:16,000 --> 01:20:16,840
Listen.

899
01:20:17,399 --> 01:20:18,760
Peeranut told me

900
01:20:19,720 --> 01:20:22,640
that the script
is based on his experience.

901
01:20:23,560 --> 01:20:25,239
I never thought

902
01:20:25,319 --> 01:20:29,720
he would find an actor
who looked so similar to his senior.

903
01:20:31,359 --> 01:20:33,039
Do you know Nut?

904
01:20:33,720 --> 01:20:34,720
Of course.

905
01:20:35,199 --> 01:20:36,439
Look.

906
01:20:36,520 --> 01:20:38,640
I even know his parents,

907
01:20:38,720 --> 01:20:41,520
let alone him.

908
01:20:42,159 --> 01:20:43,520
I was afraid

909
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:48,000
his puppy love was going to stop him
from graduating.

910
01:20:49,520 --> 01:20:51,319
Why? What happened?

911
01:20:51,880 --> 01:20:53,479
He got a boyfriend.

912
01:20:53,560 --> 01:20:56,279
Luckily, I stopped him in time.

913
01:20:57,359 --> 01:20:59,119
Do you know his boyfriend?

914
01:20:59,960 --> 01:21:00,960
Look.

915
01:21:01,039 --> 01:21:04,159
I took care of Peeranut
as if he was my own son.

916
01:21:04,239 --> 01:21:05,720
-What was his name?
-I…

917
01:21:06,279 --> 01:21:07,680
He was Anont's best friend.

918
01:21:07,760 --> 01:21:09,520
-His name was--
-Tofu.

919
01:21:10,960 --> 01:21:12,279
You're here.

920
01:21:18,159 --> 01:21:19,039
My goodness.

921
01:21:19,520 --> 01:21:21,399
You interrupted our conversation.

922
01:21:21,479 --> 01:21:23,359
Were you afraid I would say something?

923
01:21:24,039 --> 01:21:25,199
No.

924
01:21:26,039 --> 01:21:28,159
I just hate it when people talk
behind my back,

925
01:21:28,239 --> 01:21:29,520
the way they used to.

926
01:21:30,119 --> 01:21:31,079
Listen.

927
01:21:31,159 --> 01:21:34,760
If that's your way
of calling me a busybody,

928
01:21:34,840 --> 01:21:37,159
you should know that I meant well.

929
01:21:38,560 --> 01:21:39,520
Are you sure

930
01:21:40,520 --> 01:21:42,359
it wasn't for your own benefit?

931
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:44,000
Peeranut.

932
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:49,079
If you think badly of my goodwill,

933
01:21:49,159 --> 01:21:51,159
I want you to think again.

934
01:21:51,720 --> 01:21:54,960
You should realize
that you grew up with a good life

935
01:21:55,039 --> 01:21:58,680
because I pulled you back on track.

936
01:21:59,399 --> 01:22:00,439
Yes.

937
01:22:01,439 --> 01:22:03,039
You are partly the reason

938
01:22:03,800 --> 01:22:05,119
my life is like this.

939
01:22:07,439 --> 01:22:08,680
Thank you so much.

940
01:22:10,680 --> 01:22:11,840
Let's go, Tofu.

941
01:22:20,560 --> 01:22:21,600
Nut.

942
01:22:23,119 --> 01:22:24,600
Why did you go back to the club?

943
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:27,159
I forgot my phone.

944
01:22:28,319 --> 01:22:30,239
What did she say to you?

945
01:22:30,800 --> 01:22:32,199
Nothing much.

946
01:22:32,279 --> 01:22:34,119
She asked why I look like Neung.

947
01:22:39,359 --> 01:22:41,039
Don't listen

948
01:22:41,119 --> 01:22:42,520
to anything she says.

949
01:22:45,439 --> 01:22:47,520
She's a dictator

950
01:22:48,319 --> 01:22:50,039
who thinks she's always right.

951
01:22:55,359 --> 01:22:57,079
Go back to the shoot first.

952
01:22:57,159 --> 01:22:58,520
I'm going to the toilet.

953
01:23:12,359 --> 01:23:15,520
It's okay. I'll ask Song myself.

954
01:23:22,239 --> 01:23:23,279
Sir.

955
01:23:24,880 --> 01:23:27,319
Song told me
he was shooting his series here.

956
01:23:27,800 --> 01:23:29,279
Hey.

957
01:23:29,359 --> 01:23:30,479
Can I ask you something?

958
01:23:31,319 --> 01:23:34,039
Has Song complained
or come to you for advice?

959
01:23:37,159 --> 01:23:38,560
No.

960
01:23:39,119 --> 01:23:41,000
Song is a talented guy.

961
01:23:41,079 --> 01:23:43,079
He's my hero.

962
01:23:43,159 --> 01:23:46,239
If someone were to ask for advice,
it would be me.

963
01:23:46,319 --> 01:23:49,680
Song used to call Neung his hero.

964
01:23:50,199 --> 01:23:53,439
Today, someone who looks like Neung
is calling Song a hero.

965
01:23:53,960 --> 01:23:55,680
It's a little weird to me.

966
01:23:57,159 --> 01:23:59,159
But Song is really my hero.

967
01:24:00,039 --> 01:24:01,720
Think about it.

968
01:24:01,800 --> 01:24:03,399
How can someone be handsome,

969
01:24:03,479 --> 01:24:04,439
hardworking,

970
01:24:04,520 --> 01:24:06,119
smart,

971
01:24:06,199 --> 01:24:07,720
talented,

972
01:24:07,800 --> 01:24:08,880
good at basketball,

973
01:24:09,439 --> 01:24:10,760
and good at riding a bike?

974
01:24:10,840 --> 01:24:12,239
He's good at everything.

975
01:24:13,279 --> 01:24:14,439
Is that so?

976
01:24:16,840 --> 01:24:19,239
You might not realize how talented Song is

977
01:24:20,640 --> 01:24:23,159
because you're busy
thinking about your dead child.

978
01:24:25,439 --> 01:24:27,640
Maybe you're neglecting
the child you have left.

979
01:24:32,319 --> 01:24:34,600
What part of your life
don't I take an interest in?

980
01:24:35,119 --> 01:24:36,520
There's a lot.

981
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:38,640
You don't remember the food I like.

982
01:24:38,720 --> 01:24:41,079
You don't even remember my birthday.

983
01:24:41,159 --> 01:24:43,800
I wasn't the one who gave birth to you.

984
01:24:44,880 --> 01:24:47,079
But you always remember Neung's birthday.

985
01:24:47,720 --> 01:24:50,600
Even after he passed away,
you still remember.

986
01:24:54,600 --> 01:24:56,840
Song never told me anything.

987
01:24:58,760 --> 01:25:00,359
He's a strong person.

988
01:25:02,560 --> 01:25:04,119
But every strong person

989
01:25:05,000 --> 01:25:07,159
can get weak sometimes.

990
01:25:10,239 --> 01:25:12,079
I'm a terrible father.

991
01:25:14,359 --> 01:25:15,319
No.

992
01:25:16,439 --> 01:25:18,359
No one's perfect.

993
01:25:19,680 --> 01:25:21,279
And it's not wrong

994
01:25:21,960 --> 01:25:24,800
to mourn and miss your dead child.

995
01:25:25,800 --> 01:25:28,880
However, you can't neglect
the child you have left.

996
01:25:31,640 --> 01:25:34,359
To be forgotten while you are still alive

997
01:25:35,399 --> 01:25:38,000
hurts more than being separated by death.

998
01:25:45,039 --> 01:25:45,960
Thank you.

999
01:25:46,560 --> 01:25:49,560
Study hard and take care of the club.

1000
01:26:05,079 --> 01:26:06,119
Put this on me.

1001
01:26:16,760 --> 01:26:18,600
Now, we have one each.

1002
01:26:27,520 --> 01:26:28,840
That's it for today.

1003
01:26:39,159 --> 01:26:41,159
-Thank you so much.
-The shoot is over.

1004
01:26:42,880 --> 01:26:47,520
I said, the shoot is over.
Girls, the shoot is over.

1005
01:26:53,640 --> 01:26:54,960
Congratulations.

1006
01:26:56,039 --> 01:26:57,640
The shoot will be done soon.

1007
01:26:57,720 --> 01:26:59,520
Does this mean I won't see you anymore?

1008
01:27:00,239 --> 01:27:01,319
Yes.

1009
01:27:01,399 --> 01:27:04,399
We're going separate ways.

1010
01:27:05,479 --> 01:27:07,960
Can I live at your house then?

1011
01:27:08,520 --> 01:27:10,359
My dad will ask for your hand.

1012
01:27:10,439 --> 01:27:13,960
Jeez, as soon as your stress goes away,
you're here to annoy me.

1013
01:27:14,800 --> 01:27:16,039
Have you talked to him?

1014
01:27:19,920 --> 01:27:20,920
Not yet.

1015
01:27:22,199 --> 01:27:23,439
What are you waiting for?

1016
01:27:23,520 --> 01:27:24,760
Shall I talk to him?

1017
01:27:26,720 --> 01:27:29,239
How will you introduce yourself to him?

1018
01:27:32,159 --> 01:27:33,039
Well…

1019
01:27:33,640 --> 01:27:36,159
I'll say I'm a senior who pities you.

1020
01:27:39,119 --> 01:27:41,359
Have you heard of the phrase

1021
01:27:41,439 --> 01:27:44,760
"Pity is the foundation of love"?

1022
01:27:46,199 --> 01:27:47,439
No.

1023
01:27:47,520 --> 01:27:49,079
I've only heard of sympathy.

1024
01:28:01,039 --> 01:28:02,399
I wasn't expecting you.

1025
01:28:05,199 --> 01:28:06,439
I came to support you.

1026
01:28:08,199 --> 01:28:10,800
You've invited me many times,
but I never came.

1027
01:28:12,159 --> 01:28:13,720
You didn't tell me

1028
01:28:13,800 --> 01:28:15,359
it was a love story.

1029
01:28:18,800 --> 01:28:20,079
You don't mind, do you?

1030
01:28:21,680 --> 01:28:22,960
Of course not.

1031
01:28:23,039 --> 01:28:24,239
It's just acting.

1032
01:28:26,279 --> 01:28:27,720
You're not really gay.

1033
01:28:30,439 --> 01:28:31,720
Are you?

1034
01:28:36,279 --> 01:28:37,159
Song.

1035
01:28:38,079 --> 01:28:39,560
I'm sorry.

1036
01:28:41,640 --> 01:28:43,159
I keep breaking my promises.

1037
01:28:44,000 --> 01:28:46,159
I flew here as soon as I finished working.

1038
01:28:48,359 --> 01:28:50,359
Dad, don't worry.

1039
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:52,840
I know you are busy.

1040
01:28:56,960 --> 01:28:57,840
Song.

1041
01:28:58,920 --> 01:29:00,439
I'm not working hard

1042
01:29:02,159 --> 01:29:04,159
because the victim is Neung's friend.

1043
01:29:04,239 --> 01:29:06,319
I would do the same with any case.

1044
01:29:09,239 --> 01:29:10,920
I'm sorry

1045
01:29:11,960 --> 01:29:13,119
if I hurt your feelings.

1046
01:29:18,640 --> 01:29:19,600
In the past,

1047
01:29:19,680 --> 01:29:21,960
I've neglected you

1048
01:29:23,279 --> 01:29:25,399
because I knew you could
take care of yourself.

1049
01:29:26,640 --> 01:29:28,319
But the truth is, deep down,

1050
01:29:28,960 --> 01:29:30,399
you're still a puppy

1051
01:29:31,359 --> 01:29:33,159
who needs his daddy, aren't you?

1052
01:29:43,479 --> 01:29:45,119
I will try

1053
01:29:46,039 --> 01:29:47,439
to be here for you more.

1054
01:29:55,439 --> 01:29:56,920
I'm sorry.

1055
01:29:58,439 --> 01:30:02,760
It's my fault
for never telling you how I feel.

1056
01:30:07,680 --> 01:30:09,199
We are going

1057
01:30:10,479 --> 01:30:12,439
to be honest with each other

1058
01:30:13,319 --> 01:30:15,880
to avoid any misunderstandings
in the future.

1059
01:30:19,560 --> 01:30:21,439
We only have each other.

1060
01:30:22,479 --> 01:30:24,119
You are my life and soul.

1061
01:30:29,479 --> 01:30:30,800
I love you.

1062
01:30:31,920 --> 01:30:33,279
I love you too.

1063
01:30:52,640 --> 01:30:53,920
Come on.

1064
01:30:54,000 --> 01:30:55,399
Let's give them some privacy.

1065
01:30:56,680 --> 01:30:57,720
Tofu.

1066
01:30:57,800 --> 01:30:59,399
Go get changed.

1067
01:30:59,479 --> 01:31:01,000
I'll wait in the car.

1068
01:31:01,079 --> 01:31:02,239
Okay.

1069
01:31:09,439 --> 01:31:10,279
Sometimes,

1070
01:31:10,359 --> 01:31:12,960
we forget that we are still breathing.

1071
01:31:14,520 --> 01:31:15,760
But it doesn't mean

1072
01:31:16,359 --> 01:31:17,880
that breathing isn't important,

1073
01:31:18,840 --> 01:31:19,880
does it?

1074
01:31:27,560 --> 01:31:29,159
Do you want to be gay?

1075
01:31:29,720 --> 01:31:31,199
Don't you want to be a man?

1076
01:31:31,279 --> 01:31:33,159
Are you and Nut in love?

1077
01:31:34,720 --> 01:31:35,720
Yes.

1078
01:31:39,239 --> 01:31:41,000
You can hate me all you want.

1079
01:31:42,039 --> 01:31:44,479
But I will never be who you want me to be.

1080
01:31:44,560 --> 01:31:46,840
Did your ex-boyfriend traumatize you

1081
01:31:47,439 --> 01:31:48,640
from dating a younger man?

1082
01:31:50,319 --> 01:31:53,600
Not all younger men are the same.
Don't generalize us.

1083
01:31:54,399 --> 01:31:56,239
Don't you have confidence in me

1084
01:31:57,399 --> 01:31:59,079
when I'm with you at all?

1085
01:33:07,720 --> 01:33:12,720
